    <div class="instruction-container">
        <h2>How to Setup Your Signature</h2>
        <ul class="step-list">
            <li><strong>Step 1: Highlight & Copy</strong><br>
                Use your mouse to highlight all text within the dashed box of the example that matches your role. Press <strong>Ctrl + C</strong> to copy. This ensures you copy the <u>formatted text</u> (including colors and fonts).
            </li>
            <li><strong>Step 2: Access Outlook Settings</strong><br>
                <strong>Desktop:</strong> Go to <em>File > Options > Mail > Signatures</em>.<br>
                <strong>Web/O365:</strong> Click the <em>Settings Gear > View all Outlook settings > Mail > Compose and reply</em>.
            </li>
            <li><strong>Step 3: Paste as Formatted Text</strong><br>
                Click into the signature edit box and press <strong>Ctrl + V</strong>. If a small icon appears after pasting, ensure <strong>"Keep Source Formatting"</strong> is selected.
            </li>
            <li><strong>Step 4: Personalize Your Details</strong><br>
                Replace "John Doe" with your full name. Update the Job Title, Region, and Mobile number. Ensure your email address is correctly hyperlinked.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="warning-note">
            <strong>Important:</strong> Do not manually add the InfyStrat logo or legal disclaimers. These are automatically attached by the central Exchange server to ensure a uniform global footer.
        </div>
    </div>

